\begin_layout Frame
The binomial distribution is based on a 
\emph on
Bernoulli trial
\emph default
, which is a random experiment in which there are only two possible outcomes:
 success (S ) and failure (F).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
We conduct the Bernoulli trial and let
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
X=\begin{cases}
1 & \text{if the outcome is }S\\
0 & {\rm \text{if the outcome is }}F
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
Then 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 is called a 
\series bold
Bernoulli random variable
\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
If the probability of success is 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 then the probability of failure must be 
\begin_inset Formula $1−p=q$
\end_inset

, then the pmf of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 is
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f(x)=p^{x}(1-p)^{1-x},\quad x=0,1
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
It is easy to calculate 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu={\rm E}X=p,\ \sigma^{2}=pq$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $M(t)=pe^{t}+q$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator parbreak
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Binomial Experiment
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
The binomial experiment has three defining properties: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Bernoulli trials are conducted 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 times, 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
the trials are independent, 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
the probability of success 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 does not change between trials.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator parbreak
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Binomial Distribution
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
If 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 is the 
\emph on
number of successes
\emph default
 in 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 Bernoulli trials, then 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 is a 
\series bold
Binomial Random Variable
\series default
, and is denoted by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
X\sim{\rm Bin}(n,p)
\]

\end_inset

The pmf is:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f(x)={n \choose x}p^{x}(1-p)^{n-x}(x=0,1,\cdots,n)
\]

\end_inset

 Mean 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu=np$
\end_inset

, variance 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma^{2}=np(1-p)$
\end_inset

, mgf 
\begin_inset Formula $M(t)=(pe^{t}+q)^{n}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
